SIMPLE: ingratitude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ingratitude
<hw>In*grat"i*tude</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>ingratitude</ets>, L. <ets>ingratitudo</ets>. See
<er>Ingrate</er>.]</ety> <def>Lack of gratitude; insensibility to,
forgetfulness of, or ill return for, kindness or favors received;
unthankfulness; ungratefulness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ingratitude</qex>, thou marble-hearted fiend.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Ingratitude</qex> is abhorred both by God and man.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ingrave</ent>⟦br⟧
